I love all four movies, but I can't give it a five. Even though there was a Digital Ultraviolet card for all four movies, I could only download the digital version of two of the movies (Jailhouse Rock and GI Blues), and two could not be downloaded (King Creole and Viva Las Vegas, arguably Elvis' best movie). I tried using different Websites, Flixter and VuDu. Flixter said that King Creole and Viva Las Vegas weren't available for Download. VuDu said all four movies were available, but I could only download Jailhouse Rock and GI Blues.

I had a long flight to Osaka and wanted to watch the four films on my iPad during the trip.  Unfortunately, I could only watch two of them.

This is probably the BEST of the Elvis Presley 4-movie sets on the market. "King Creole," "Jailhouse Rock," and "Viva Las Vegas" are all among his top 10 best quality movies. Those 3 films are also among his best movie soundtracks. "G.I. Blues" is at least mid-level quality so it's not too big a drag on the set, and has a few decent songs in it too. All 4 of these films are from roughly the first half of Elvis's movie career, and most of his better films are from that time. The other Elvis films that are among his best are "Flaming Star," "Wild in the Country," "Loving You," "Speedway," and "Follow That Dream." So, get this set and you'll be well on your way to having all of the King's best movies!
